author: CNN
description: Podcaster Theo Von called out the Department of Homeland Security for using footage of him to tout deportations in a video that since appears to have been removed from DHS’ account on the social media platform X.
title: Theo Von to DHS: Stop using my video

author: CNN
description: Security camera footage shows an armed robbery at Heller Jewelers in San Ramon, California Monday afternoon. The suspects stole approximately $1 million dollars, according to police.
title: Armed robbers steal $1 million worth of jewelry at store in California

author: CNN
description: Botswana is moving to reduce its dependence on diamonds by diversifying within the mining sector, tapping into rare earths and other minerals while ensuring in-country processing to create jobs and add value. Officials say natural diamonds will remain central, marketed for their rarity and provenance to stand apart from synthetics. The country is also working to expand intra-African trade through new trade corridors and digital platforms that make commerce more seamless across borders.  #CNN #News
title: Botswana shifts economic strategy amid surging demand for lab-grown diamonds

author: CNN
description: Global trade is shifting as countries diversify away from reliance on the U.S. and China, WTO officials say. The WTO praised China for giving up developing-country trade perks, calling it a step toward fairness. DP World reported a 20% revenue boost and $2.5 billion in new investments, with its chairman noting that tariff disputes bring both disruption and opportunity.  #CNN #News
title: 'It's been bent, but there is a stable core that is still resilient': WTO chief on global trade

author: CNN
description: The White House posted a video of its new “Presidential Walk of Fame,” featuring gold-framed portraits of past presidents. However, the video shows a photo of an autopen signature instead of a portrait of the 46th president himself. A spokesperson for Biden declined to comment on the new display.
title: White House hangs photo of Biden autopen signature instead of portrait

author: CNN
description: New York Mets announcer Gary Cohen expressed his surprise during a Mets-Cubs game after he found out Chicago Cubs player Matt Shaw missed a game to go to Charlie Kirk's funeral.
title: Mets announcer criticizes Cubs player for missing game for Kirk memorial

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump has been busy making design changes to the White House, from the Rose Garden to the Oval Office, many of the choices are reminiscent of his Palm Beach resort Mar-a-Lago.
title: Trump's latest WH renovations include 'Presidential Walk of Fame'

author: CNN
description: Federal prosecutors are nearing a decision whether to bring possible perjury charges against former FBI Director James Comey, with a legal deadline expiring on Tuesday, according to people familiar with the investigation. The probe, run by federal prosecutors at the US Attorney’s Office for Virginia’s eastern district, is examining whether Comey made false statements during his September, 30, 2020, testimony to Congress on his handling of the investigation into Russian meddling in the 2016 US presidential election, people familiar with the matter said. Prosecutors, under criminal law, generally would only have five years to the day to bring a charge. #CNN #News
title: Sources: DOJ nearing decision on charging James Comey with perjury

author: CNN
description: Secretary of State Marco Rubio held a brief 15-minute meeting with Russian Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov, urging Moscow to take "meaningful steps" toward a lasting resolution in Ukraine, according to the State Department. Lavrov offered no public response, though he gave a thumbs-up to cameras as he exited. The high-stakes meeting came just hours after Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky addressed the United Nations, warning that global institutions have been too weak to stop wars and calling for urgent action to halt Russia’s aggression.   #CNN #News
title: 'Action is what Putin responds to': Gimenez on US's precarious position in Russia-Ukraine war

author: CNN
description: After almost a week off air, Jimmy Kimmel returned to his late-night stage Tuesday night. The episode featured a diverse array of special guests and a nod to a past talk show host.
title: Jimmy Kimmel’s monologue had hidden Easter egg

author: CNN
description: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky spoke to the UN General Assembly to issue a warning and plea to the world, stressing the need for military aid in order to keep fighting Russia. #CNN #News
title: Zelensky addresses UN General Assembly, asks for support against Russia

author: CNN
description: Two detainees are dead and another is in serious condition following a shooting at a US Immigration and Customs Enforcement field office in Dallas, according to a Department of Homeland Security spokesperson. CNN Senior National Correspondent Ed Lavandera reports from near the detention facility in Texas.
title: Details emerge in fatal shooting of ICE detainees in Dallas

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump said Ukraine could restore its borders from before Russia’s invasion and that he believes NATO member countries should shoot down Russian aircraft if they enter their airspace, escalating his rhetoric against the Kremlin as its war in Ukraine drags on. #CNN #News
title: Trump: Ukraine can take back land from Russia

author: CNN
description: Jimmy Kimmel returned to his late-night stage and urged viewers to stand up to President Trump’s threats, even as Trump sent out a new social media attack against Kimmel’s network, ABC. In his monologue, Kimmel assailed “anti-American” efforts to curtail free speech in the United States and signaled that he won’t temper his criticism of the president after a nearly week-long suspension of his show amid pressure from the Trump administration. #CNN #News
title: Jimmy Kimmel defends free speech in emotional return

author: CNN
description: Citing a need for “friend and weapons,” Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky spoke to the UN General Assembly, asking for support against Russian aggression.
title: Zelensky implores United Nations to help stop Russia

author: CNN
description: At least one victim is dead and two others are injured after a shooting at a US Immigration and Customs Enforcement field office in Dallas, according to authorities. #CNN #News
title: 1 dead, at least 2 injured in Dallas ICE facility shooting

author: CNN
description: A CNN investigation finds more than 100 American children left stranded after ICE took their parents. CNN’s Kyung Lah follows one family’s story of separation and resilience from Texas to Honduras. #CNN #News
title: What happens to American kids when their parents are deported

author: CNN
description: One person is dead and two others have been hospitalized with gunshot wounds after a shooting at an US Immigration and Customs Enforcement facility in Dallas on Wednesday morning, according to police. A suspect is dead from a self-inflicted gun shot wound, according to Homeland Security Secretary Kristi Noem. #cnn #news
title: 1 dead after shooting at Dallas ICE facility

author: CNN
description:
Jimmy Kimmel returned to his late-night stage Tuesday night after the host was suspended for making remarks about Charlie Kirk's death. ABC's reinstatement of Kimmel was celebrated among late-night hosts.

#cnn #news #trump
title: Late-night hosts react to Jimmy Kimmel's return

author: CNN
description: Typhoon Ragasa left a trail of damage across Hong Kong and parts of southern China Wednesday. Across all of Hong Kong, 82 people were injured and over 800 people took refuge in temporary shelters across the territory, according to authorities. #cnn #news
title: Typhoon Ragasa wreaks havoc in Hong Kong

author: CNN
description: In central Bangkok a large sinkhole 50-meters deep opened up near a hospital and police station. According to the Tai prime minister underground construction to a train line was the cause. No injuries were reported, according to Reuters.
title: Massive sinkhole swallows cars in Thailand

author: CNN
description: The cast of Dawson's Creek reunited on Tuesday to honor James Van Der Beek, who revealed that he has stage three colorectal cancer last year. Katie Holmes, Joshua Jackson, and Michelle Williams came together to raise money for the nonprofit F Cancer, with Van Der Beek joining virtually.
title: 'Dawson's Creek' cast reunites and honors James Van Der Beek

author: CNN
description: Evangelical Christians across social media have been posting videos claiming the rapture is near. CNN's Max Foster explains what caused the trend. #CNN #news
title: What is Rapture Tok?

author: CNN
description: Rep. James Clyburn (D-SC) was one of dozens of Democrats who voted "no" on the House resolution to honor Charlie Kirk's legacy, saying honoring a life compared to honoring a legacy are very different. Clyburn explained he could not accept Kirk's comments on race and his opposition to affirmative action. #CNN #News #charliekirk
title: Rep. Clyburn: I'll never vote to honor Charlie Kirk's legacy

author: CNN
description: Ryan Routh, the 59-year-old accused of attempting to kill Donald Trump as the former and future president played a round of golf on his Florida course last year – the second attempt on Trump’s life during his second campaign – has been found guilty on all charges against him. Routh tried to stab himself in the neck with a pen after the verdict was read, but authorities stopped him. CNN's Randi Kaye reports. #CNN #news
title: Would-be Trump assassin tries to stab himself in neck after guilty verdict

author: CNN
description: Catastrophic flooding hit eastern Taiwan's Hualien County after Typhoon Ragasa dumped more than a foot of rain on the island. The flooding has submerged entire neighborhoods, with many residents reported missing. #CNN #News #TyphoonRagasa
title: Typhoon Ragasa causes deadly flooding in Taiwan

author: CNN
description: Jimmy Kimmel returned to his late-night stage and gave an impassioned monologue about standing up against "anti-American" attempts to attack free speech.
title: What Kimmel said about Charlie Kirk and free speech

author: CNN
description: President Trump’s visit to the UN started with a technical error when an escalator stalled immediately while he was getting on it. A UN spokesperson explained that it was unintentional and likely caused by someone brushing up against a “built-in safety mechanism.” #cnn #news #unga #trump
title: Trump’s escalator fiasco at UNGA

author: CNN
description: The seaside Fullerton Ocean Park hotel in Hong Kong appeared to be hit by storm surges, shattering its glass doors. #cnn #news #hongkong #ragasa #typhoonragasa
title: Rush of water blasts through Hong Kong hotel windows

author: CNN
description: CNN's Hanako Montgomery reports from Hong Kong where Typhoon Ragasa has hit, with winds reported to reach 100 mph. #CNN #News #TyphoonRagasa
title: Typhoon Ragasa hits Hong Kong with 100 mph winds

author: CNN
description: CNN's Paula Hancocks spotlights the stories of Palestinians struggling to evacuate Gaza City amid ongoing Israeli assaults, including Abu Wissam who lacks the necessary funds to do so after losing his son and home. #cnn #news #gazacity #gaza
title: Why are hundreds of thousands unable to leave Gaza City?
